<body>
<h1>DOs</h1>

<p>
<ul>
<li>PASSPORTS PASSPORTS PASSPORTS. Make sure your passport is valid for 6 months after the date you intend to leave the country. You will need to have at least 2 blank pages for every country you intend to travel to.</li>
<li>VISAS. Check this <a href="">link to website</a> for details</li>
<li>CLOTHES. A lot of people don't realise how cold it gets in the evenings. You will most likely spend a lot of time outdoors so take some warm clothes as well. One word. LAYERS.</li>
<li>SUNCREAM. Typically a difficult one to find when you're there, so take some with you.</li>
<li>TORCH. Power cuts are quite frequent.</li>
<li>LIP BALM. An essential to protect against the dry African air, the wind in your face and the insane amount of dust during dry season.</li>
</ul>
</p>

<h2>DONTs</h2>
<p>
<ul>
<li>BE A CREATURE OF HABIT. Try as many local cuisines as you can.</li>
<li>BE CARELESS WITH YOUR BELONGINGS. Awareness please.</li>
<li></li>
<li></li>
<li></li>
<li></li>
</ul>
</p>



